Next, $n + 31 = 37$. We need all positive integers $a$ such that there exists a set $X$ of 6 integers where for every $k = 1, \ldots, 36$, $ax + y \equiv k \pmod{37}$ for some $x, y \in X$. The condition requires $\{ax + y \mod 37 \mid x, y \in X\} = \{1, \ldots, 36\}$. Since $|X \times X| = 36$, this set must exactly cover all non-zero residues modulo 37.

